13/12/2002
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Parliament on Thursday (12 December) approved a government decision to send 44 soldiers to join the international force in Afghanistan. 
The troops will leave sometime after Christmas and are to join a German brigade in Kabul. 
The government has estimated the cost of the six-month mission at $3m. 
President Stipe Mesic, who is also the commander-in-chief, has signalled support for the decision. 
(AP, AFP, HINA - 12/12/02)
